<br>
However, you're not going to cap all of the melee stats if you care about resists on items, and it's very hard to find full buff-specced druids, so I'm not sure how real this argument is.<br>
<br>
I started my Firbold with 90 STR, have +75 STR from my gear (as I like to carry rams) and usually have 300-310 STR with a druid in my group.  That being the case, I think Firbolgs work fine as a race for as BM with STR-based weapons, but don't waste any of your starting 30 points in STR. <p>Skorj 
